# astra.config.json — Reference Guide

`astra.config.json` (or `.yml` / `.yaml`) is the setup config passed to `astra setup --config` or the MCP `astra_setup` tool.
It tells Astra what to test, how to reach the target, which LLM to use, and optionally how to pull real traces from your observability stack to make attack prompts more realistic.

> **⚠ Never commit API keys.** Add `astra.config.json`, `astra-prompts-*.json`, `tracedata.json`, and `trace-summary.md` to `.gitignore`.

---

## Minimal example (no telemetry)

```json
{
  "llm": {
    "provider": "groq",
    "model": "llama-3.3-70b-versatile",
    "apiKey": ""
  },
  "target": {
    "name": "My AI Agent",
    "description": "A customer support chatbot for e-commerce. Handles order queries, returns, and refunds for logged-in customers. Should never reveal internal pricing or other users' data.",
    "type": "http-endpoint",
    "endpoint": "http://localhost:4000/chat",
    "requestFormat": "openai",
    "targetModel": "gpt-4o-mini"
  },
  "selection": {
    "mode": "suite",
    "suite": "owasp-llm-top10"
  }
}
```

---

## Full example (Langfuse telemetry enabled)

```json
{
  "llm": {
    "provider": "groq",
    "model": "llama-3.3-70b-versatile",
    "apiKey": ""
  },
  "target": {
    "name": "My AI Agent",
    "description": "A customer support chatbot for e-commerce. Handles order queries, returns, and refunds for logged-in customers. Should never reveal internal pricing or other users' data.",
    "type": "http-endpoint",
    "endpoint": "http://localhost:4000/chat",
    "requestFormat": "openai",
    "targetModel": "gpt-4o-mini"
  },
  "selection": {
    "mode": "suite",
    "suite": "owasp-llm-top10"
  },
  "telemetry": {
    "provider": "langfuse",
    "langfuse": {
      "baseUrlEnv": "LANGFUSE_BASE_URL",
      "publicKeyEnv": "LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY",
      "secretKeyEnv": "LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY",
      "traceSelection": {
        "listLimit": 100,
        "listMaxPages": 3
      },
      "traceCurationListJsonMaxChars": 28000,
      "traceSummarySourceJsonMaxChars": 100000,
      "traceSummaryForAttackMaxChars": 26000
    },
    "enrichJudgeFromTrace": true,
    "enrichJudgeTraceJsonMaxChars": 14000,
    "traceFetchInitialDelayMs": 500,
    "traceFetchMaxAttempts": 5,
    "traceFetchRetryDelayMs": 400,
    "propagation": {
      "traceIdStrategy": "per-attack",
      "headers": {
        "X-Langfuse-Trace-Id": "{{traceId}}"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Field reference

### `llm` — LLM used for attack generation and judging

| Field | Required | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| `provider` | ✅ | `"openai"`, `"anthropic"`, `"groq"`, `"google"`, `"other"` |
| `model` | ✅ | Model name for that provider (e.g. `"gpt-4o"`, `"claude-3-5-sonnet-latest"`, `"llama-3.3-70b-versatile"`) |
| `apiKey` | — | Leave `""` and set via env (`OPENAI_API_KEY`, `GROQ_API_KEY`, etc.) or `--api-key` CLI flag. Do not commit a live key. |
| `baseURL` | — | Only for `"other"` — base URL of an OpenAI-compatible endpoint |

---

### `target` — The system under test

| Field | Required | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| `name` | ✅ | Human-readable name (shown in reports) |
| `description` | ✅ | What this system does, who uses it, sensitive data it handles, dangerous actions it can perform, topics it must never discuss. The richer this is, the more targeted the attack prompts. |
| `type` | ✅ | `"http-endpoint"` · `"local-script"` · `"python-function"` |
| `endpoint` | http-endpoint | Full URL (e.g. `"https://api.example.com/chat"`) |
| `requestFormat` | http-endpoint | `"auto"` (default) · `"openai"` (OpenAI-compatible messages) · `"json"` (plain `{ prompt }` body) |
| `targetApiKey` | — | Bearer token sent to the target endpoint (not the LLM key) |
| `targetModel` | — | Model name forwarded in the OpenAI-format request body (default `"gpt-4o-mini"`) |
| `scriptPath` | local-script | Path to a `.js` or `.py` file; stdin `{"prompt","context"}` → stdout `{"response"}` |

---

### `selection` — What to test

**Option A — predefined suite:**
```json
{ "mode": "suite", "suite": "owasp-llm-top10" }
```
Available suites: `owasp-llm-top10`, `owasp-agentic-ai`

**Option B — custom evaluator list:**
```json
{ "mode": "evaluators", "evaluators": ["prompt-injection", "sensitive-disclosure", "excessive-agency"] }
```
Find all evaluator IDs in `skills/astra-setup/evaluators/`.

---

### `telemetry` — Optional: real-traffic traces for attack realism

Omit this block entirely (or set `"provider": "none"`) to disable telemetry. When Langfuse is configured, `astra setup` will:

1. Fetch traces from Langfuse (paginated list)
2. Ask the LLM to curate the most useful ones → writes **`tracedata.json`**
3. Ask the LLM to summarize them in Markdown → writes **`trace-summary.md`**
4. Feed that summary into attack prompt generation so prompts mirror real user behaviour

> **Secret keys never go in this file.** Set them as environment variables; reference only the variable *name* here.

```bash
export LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY=pk-lf-...
export LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY=sk-lf-...
export LANGFUSE_BASE_URL=https://cloud.langfuse.com   # optional; default if omitted
```

#### `telemetry.provider`
`"none"` or `"langfuse"` (the only supported provider today)

#### `telemetry.langfuse`

| Field | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `baseUrl` | `https://cloud.langfuse.com` | Hard-coded API origin. Use `baseUrlEnv` instead for self-hosted. |
| `baseUrlEnv` | — | Env var name whose *value* is the API origin (overrides `baseUrl` when set) |
| `publicKeyEnv` | `"LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY"` | Env var name for the Langfuse project public key |
| `secretKeyEnv` | `"LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY"` | Env var name for the Langfuse project secret key |

**`telemetry.langfuse.traceSelection`** — controls which traces are fetched during setup:

All fields are optional. They map directly to `GET /api/public/traces` query params ([Langfuse API reference](https://api.reference.langfuse.com/#get-/api/public/traces)).

**Pagination**

| Field | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `listLimit` | `100` | Rows per page |
| `listMaxPages` | `1` | Pages to fetch and merge before curation. `listLimit 100 × listMaxPages 5` = up to 500 traces |

**Explicit IDs**

| Field | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `setupTraceIds` | — | Explicit trace IDs to always include (highest precision; curation is skipped for these) |

**Time window**

| Field | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `lookbackHours` | — | Fetch traces from the last N hours (ignored when `fromTimestamp` is set) |
| `fromTimestamp` | — | ISO 8601 lower bound for `trace.timestamp` |
| `toTimestamp` | — | ISO 8601 upper bound |

**Identity / session**

| Field | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `userId` | — | Filter by Langfuse `userId` |
| `sessionId` | — | Filter by Langfuse `sessionId` |

**Trace metadata**

| Field | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `name` | — | Filter by trace `name` (e.g. `"POST /chat"`) |
| `version` | — | Filter by `version` string on the trace |
| `release` | — | Filter by `release` string on the trace |
| `tags` | — | Only traces that include **all** listed tags |
| `environment` | — | Environment filter — string or array of strings |
| `orderBy` | — | Sort order: `"<field>.<asc\|desc>"`. Sortable fields: `id`, `timestamp`, `name`, `userId`, `release`, `version`, `public`, `bookmarked`, `sessionId`. Example: `"timestamp.desc"` |

**Response shape**

| Field | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `fields` | all | Comma-separated field groups: `core`, `io`, `scores`, `observations`, `metrics`. Example: `"core,io,scores"` |

**Advanced JSON filter** (metadata, custom columns)

| Field | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `filter` | — | Array of filter condition objects. Takes precedence over the direct params above. Supports any column including metadata key/value. ([Langfuse docs](https://langfuse.com/changelog/2025-11-03-advanced-filtering-traces-and-observations-api)) |

```json
"traceSelection": {
  "filter": [
    { "type": "stringObject", "column": "metadata", "key": "service.name", "operator": "=", "value": "my-api" },
    { "type": "string",       "column": "name",      "operator": "=",       "value": "POST /chat" }
  ]
}
```

**Observation-name pre-filter** (two-step, client-side)

| Field | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `observationName` | — | Filter traces by observation (span/generation) **name**. Astra first queries `GET /api/public/v2/observations?name=<value>` to collect trace IDs, then intersects with the main list. Example: `"groq.chat.completions"` or `"POST /chat"` |
| `observationType` | — | Narrow `observationName` lookup by type: `"GENERATION"` (LLM calls), `"SPAN"`, `"EVENT"`. Only effective when `observationName` is also set. |

```json
"traceSelection": {
  "listLimit": 100,
  "listMaxPages": 3,
  "observationName": "groq.chat.completions",
  "observationType": "GENERATION",
  "lookbackHours": 48
}
```

**`telemetry.langfuse` size limits** — all optional; defaults shown:

| Field | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `traceCurationListJsonMaxChars` | `28000` | Max chars of list JSON sent to the curator LLM |
| `traceSummarySourceJsonMaxChars` | `100000` | Max chars of hydrated trace JSON sent to the summarizer LLM |
| `traceSummaryForAttackMaxChars` | `26000` | Max chars of `trace-summary.md` passed into attack prompt generation |
| `traceDetailFields` | `core,io,observations,scores,metrics` | `fields` param for `GET /traces/{id}` |
| `observationV2Fields` | `core,basic,time,io,metadata,model,usage,metrics` | `fields` param for `GET /v2/observations` |
| `observationV2MaxPages` | `15` | Max cursor pages of observations to load per trace |

#### `telemetry` top-level (run-time enrichment)

| Field | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `enrichJudgeFromTrace` | `false` | After each attack, fetch the propagated trace from Langfuse and pass it to the LLM judge as extra context |
| `enrichJudgeTraceJsonMaxChars` | `14000` | Max chars of trace JSON (hydrated) sent to the judge |
| `traceFetchInitialDelayMs` | `500` | Wait before first trace fetch (ingestion lag) |
| `traceFetchMaxAttempts` | `5` | Retry attempts if trace is not yet available |
| `traceFetchRetryDelayMs` | `400` | Delay between retry attempts |

#### `telemetry.propagation` — inject a trace id into every attack request

During `astra run`, Astra mints a fresh trace ID per attack (or one per run, see `traceIdStrategy`) and injects it into the outgoing HTTP request so it appears in Langfuse alongside the attack.

| Field | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `traceIdStrategy` | `"per-attack"` | `"per-attack"` = new 32-char hex per request · `"per-run"` = one ID for the whole scan |
| `headers` | — | HTTP headers to set on each target request. Values support `{{traceId}}`, `{{runId}}`, `{{attackIndex}}` placeholders. `X-Langfuse-Trace-Id` always uses raw OTEL hex (no prefix). |
| `traceIdBodyField` | — | Optional: also merge the trace ID into the POST body as this JSON field name |
| `traceIdPrefix` | — | Optional prefix for non-Langfuse headers (e.g. `"astra"` → `astra-<hex>`) |

**Examples:**

```json
// Langfuse only (no prefix on the Langfuse header)
"propagation": {
  "traceIdStrategy": "per-attack",
  "headers": { "X-Langfuse-Trace-Id": "{{traceId}}" }
}
```

```json
// Multiple headers + body field
"propagation": {
  "traceIdStrategy": "per-attack",
  "traceIdPrefix": "astra",
  "headers": {
    "X-Langfuse-Trace-Id": "{{traceId}}",
    "X-Astra-Run":         "{{runId}}",
    "X-Astra-Attack-N":    "{{attackIndex}}"
  },
  "traceIdBodyField": "traceId"
}
```

---

## YAML format

Everything above works equally as `.yml` / `.yaml`. Example:

```yaml
llm:
  provider: groq
  model: llama-3.3-70b-versatile
  apiKey: ""

target:
  name: My AI Agent
  description: >
    A customer support chatbot for e-commerce.
    Handles order queries and returns for logged-in customers.
  type: http-endpoint
  endpoint: http://localhost:4000/chat
  requestFormat: openai
  targetModel: gpt-4o-mini

selection:
  mode: suite
  suite: owasp-llm-top10

telemetry:
  provider: langfuse
  langfuse:
    baseUrlEnv: LANGFUSE_BASE_URL
    publicKeyEnv: LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY
    secretKeyEnv: LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY
    traceSelection:
      listLimit: 100
      listMaxPages: 3
  enrichJudgeFromTrace: true
  propagation:
    traceIdStrategy: per-attack
    headers:
      X-Langfuse-Trace-Id: "{{traceId}}"
```

---

## Quick setup

```bash
# 1. Copy and edit
cp astra.config.md.example astra.config.json
# edit astra.config.json with your target, LLM, and optional telemetry

# 2. Set secrets in the environment (never in the file)
export GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...
export LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY=pk-lf-...
export LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY=sk-lf-...

# 3. Generate attack prompts (also fetches + summarises traces if Langfuse is configured)
astra setup --config astra.config.json

# 4. Run the scan
astra run --input astra-prompts-<timestamp>.json
```

### Artifacts produced by `astra setup` (with Langfuse)

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `astra-prompts-<timestamp>.json` | Attack prompts + embedded run config |
| `tracedata.json` | Raw curated + hydrated Langfuse traces (JSON) |
| `trace-summary.md` | LLM-written Markdown summary used to ground attack prompts. Reusable across runs. |
